## Executive Overview

The BOEING 220-G TELECOM CORE NODE represents the second-generation evolution of the STRIKE CORE platform, marking the transition from endurance-focused flight experimentation to **persistent aerospace telecommunications infrastructure**.

Where the STRIKE CORE validated long-duration atmospheric stability, the TELECOM CORE NODE introduces:

* Persistent airborne communications architecture
* Distributed signal routing intelligence
* Multi-domain relay redundancy
* Early lattice-based structural augmentation
* First-generation NEO CORE integration

The platform’s central shift is conceptual:

> From “staying airborne” → to “remaining continuously connected”

---

## 1. Development Objectives

The TELECOM CORE NODE was designed around five operational transformations:

### Persistent Connectivity

Maintain uninterrupted multi-domain communication coverage across:

* Airborne assets
* Maritime networks
* Remote terrestrial nodes
* Satellite uplinks

### Signal Intelligence Integration

Introduce predictive communication routing.

### Structural Adaptation

Begin early distributed-load experimentation.

### Energy Reallocation

Prioritize onboard systems for communications over propulsion optimization.

### Network Resilience

Ensure multi-path redundancy under failure conditions.

